â€œWhereâ€™s the space?â€



â€œWhoâ€™s the extra player and how are we using them?â€



â€œWhat could you have done before receiving the ball?â€



â€œCan we switch the play earlier?â€

Iâ€™ve found that these short, focused questions stick better than long explanations. Players stay involved and reflect in action.






